e Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh Filiol married Hugh Filiol before 1310, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","before 1310":"enne 1310","1310":"1310","1280":"1280","Europe":"Europe","Dorsetshire, England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1310":"ennen vuotta 1310","1310":"1310","1280":"1280","Europe":"Europe","Dorsetshire, England":"Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1280–Male":"1280–Décédé","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","before 1310":"avant 1310","1310":"1310","1280":"1280","Europe":"Europe","Dorsetshire, England":"Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh Filiol a épousé Hugh Filiol avant 1310, à Europe. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1280–Male":"1280–Verstorben","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","before 1310":"vor 1310","1310":"1310","1280":"1280","Europe":"Europa","Dorsetshire, England":"Dorset, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh Filiol hat vor 1310 in Europa Hug